modules.description: This module implements a PostgreSQL-backed session store with asynchronous I/O using connection pooling via a throttle. It provides operations to generate, retrieve, set, and clear session data with optional expiration periods. The module works with string keys and values, and expects a predefined database schema with appropriate tables and indexes.

This module implements a PostgreSQL-backed session store with asynchronous I/O, supporting operations to generate, retrieve, set, and clear session data using string keys and values. It includes a pooling submodule that manages multiple connections efficiently via a throttle, allowing controlled concurrency and resource usage. The module uses a predefined database schema with required tables and indexes, and supports session expiration with a default one-week period. Example usage includes storing user session data asynchronously and managing session lifetimes through optional expiration settings.
